  "text": "There are many suggestions that there is a common mechanism for representing approximate numerosity in animals and humans [CITATION_1] . However, human quantification skills are much more advanced than those of animals. We not only estimate and perceive numerosity but we can count, i.e. enumerate objects by tagging them by numbers' names [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] .",
